The proceedings upon the main inquiry are recorded at great length on the Rolls of Parliament, and were one of the “causes celebres' of the reign. Before seu- tence was given the Earl of Gloucester had married the King's daughter, but the Earl of Hereford was also connected with the royal family. In truth‚ the occasion
